@startuml epicd-arch-class-skeleton
' epicd — Class-diagram SKELETON (input for the deferred internal-architecture pass).
' Encodes the 2026-07-04 three-plane principle: one canonical state machine +
' two read-only anti-corruption contracts (IssueSource / Coordinator) + kind-keyed
' RefineStrategy registry. This is a BACKBONE, not the final class model:
' method bodies, error handling, caching, state-management are intentionally omitted.
'
' Stereotypes: <<pure>> pure data/function ; <<contract>> anti-corruption seam ;
'              <<impl>> shipped ; <<planned>> designed/absent ; <<projection>> view-only.

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam class {
  BorderColor #555555
  BackgroundColor #E8F0FE
  BackgroundColor<<pure>> #C8E6C9
  BackgroundColor<<contract>> #FFE0B2
  BackgroundColor<<projection>> #E1BEE7
  BackgroundColor<<planned>> #FFF3E0
}

title epicd — architecture class skeleton (3 planes + 2 contracts + RefineStrategy registry)

' ============================================================
' PLANE 1 — CORE STATE MACHINE (canonical, pure, ADR-protected)
' ============================================================
package "Plane 1 · core state machine  (pure, canonical, slowest-changing)" {

  class Task <<pure>> {
    +id : string
    +pipeline_id : string             '' LANE axis (structural, ~immutable)
    +phase : string                    '' bare phase name — SOLE persisted progress axis (inert `state` DELETED)
    .. derived, NOT stored ..
    '' turn = actor(phase) [pipeline-data] ; role = from tree ; status = label(role,phase) display
    +labels : string[]                 '' kind:feature / kind:chore / kind:epic live here
    +parent_id? : string
    +refine_log? : RefineArtifact[]    '' authoring (E7)
    +dod? : ...
    +cap? : ...
  }

  class PipelineState <<pure>> {
    +name : string
    +actor : "machine" | "human" | "none"   '' generalizes actionable; turn = actor(phase)
  }
  class Pipeline <<pure>> {
    +id : string
    +states : PipelineState[]
  }

  class Interpreter <<pure>> {
    -pipelines : Map<string, Pipeline>
    -registry : Map<"pid:state", Handler>
    +register(p : Pipeline, state, h : Handler)
    +scan(tasks : Task[]) : ItemReadyEvent[]
    +dispatch(events, tasks) : Promise<void>
  }

  interface Handler <<pure>> {
    +(event : ItemReadyEvent, task : Task) : void | Promise
  }

  Pipeline "1" *-- "many" PipelineState
  Interpreter o-- Pipeline
  Interpreter o-- Handler : keyed by (pipeline_id, state)
}

note right of Interpreter
  CANONICAL vocabulary lives ONLY here.
  scan/dispatch exist today but are TEST-ONLY (src/engine/*).
  Handlers are the extension point (Plane-2 wiring + authoring strategies).
  FOUR-AXIS (2026-07-04 FINAL): per-task stores pipeline_id + bare phase.
  turn = pipelineDef[phase].actor (pipeline-data, NOT a field) · role from tree · claim runtime.
  pick-up predicate = pipelineDef[phase].actor==machine ∧ no live claim.
  `ready`/`in-progress` by claim; `needs-human` IS a phase (actor=human).
  status = label(role,phase) display only. Inert engine `state` DELETED (E1/BACK-601).
end note

' ============================================================
' AUTHORING — RefineStrategy registry (behind the authoring:Refining handler)
' ============================================================
package "Authoring extension · RefineStrategy registry  (kind selects strategy)" {

  interface RefineStrategy <<pure>> {
    +kind : "feature" | "chore" | "epic"
    +step(task : Task, artifacts) : RefineStep   '' PURE, re-entrant; cursor DERIVED (project), not a param
    '' artifacts = Task.refine_log (append-only). Detail: authoring-refine-class.puml
  }
  class RefineStep <<pure>> {
    '' produce(artifact) | review(round,target) | revise(feedback)
    '' | promote (→Backlog) | escalate (→needs-human)
  }
  class FeatureRefine <<planned>> {
    '' produce(proposal)→review(1)→[revise→review(2)]→produce(plan)→review→promote
  }
  class ChoreRefine <<planned>> {
    '' produce(checklist)→review(1)→promote
  }
  class EpicRefine <<planned>> {
    '' produce(plan)→promote (plan only, no children)
  }
  class RefineRegistry <<planned>> {
    -byKind : Map<kind, RefineStrategy>
    +register(s : RefineStrategy)
    +get(kind) : RefineStrategy
  }
  class RefiningHandler <<planned>> {
    '' the authoring:Refining Handler — thin dispatcher (Plane-2 driver)
    +(event, task) : s = registry.get(task.kind);
    ''   loop: step = s.step(task,artifacts,cursor);
    ''         PERFORM side effect (spawn reviewer/worker, write artifact, persist cursor);
    ''         on promote → advance Refining→Backlog
  }

  RefineStrategy <|.. FeatureRefine
  RefineStrategy <|.. ChoreRefine
  RefineStrategy <|.. EpicRefine
  RefineStrategy ..> RefineStep : returns
  RefineRegistry o-- RefineStrategy
  RefiningHandler ..> RefineRegistry : dispatch by kind
}
RefiningHandler ..|> Handler : registered at (authoring, "Refining")

note bottom of RefineRegistry
  BOUNDARY = intent vs mechanism. Strategy decides WHAT (RefineStep);
  RefiningHandler/driver decides HOW (which Claude Code invocation, worktree,
  retry) and PERFORMS all side effects. Strategy sees only DATA (task+artifacts
  +cursor) — no session handles/paths — so it unit-tests without a harness.
  Authoring pipeline stays MINIMAL: Draft→Refining→Backlog. Fine cycle progress
  is strategy-internal (cursor), surfaced to UI as a Coordinator runtime-fact
  (projection), NOT a pipeline state. Adding kind:inquiry = register a strategy;
  state machine & driver unchanged (pipeline-as-data / ADR-011 D-2 kept clean).
end note

' ============================================================
' PLANE 2 — EXECUTION / DRIVER (impure, externally constrained, fastest-changing)
' ============================================================
package "Plane 2 · execution-driver  (impure, external, fastest-changing)" {

  interface Coordinator <<contract>> {
    +claims() : Map<taskId, Claim>
  }
  class Claim <<pure>> {
    +driverId : string
    +field : (sourceId, pipeline_id)
    +since : timestamp
  }
  class BaimeClaimsAdapter <<planned>> {
    '' soak: projects .active-agents / .caps → claims()
  }
  class EngineClaimRegistry <<planned>> {
    '' M1+: driver/supervisor own claim state → claims()
  }

  Coordinator ..> Claim
  Coordinator <|.. BaimeClaimsAdapter
  Coordinator <|.. EngineClaimRegistry
}

note bottom of Coordinator
  ANTI-CORRUPTION SEAM. Contract SHAPE is stable across soak↔engine;
  only the adapter behind it swaps. Claim is a RUNTIME FACT, never a
  persisted phase. Claim (durable + timestamped) IS the checkout record:
  actor(phase)=machine ∧ live claim ⇒ 🤖 active ; ∧ no claim ⇒ ⏳ queued ;
  ∧ claim timed out ⇒ ⚠️ stale/orphaned. (no persisted in-progress needed)
  ONE runtime-fact channel for BOTH planes: execution claims AND authoring
  refine progress (e.g. "Refining · review cycle 2") ride here as projection.
end note

' ============================================================
' DATA PLANE — IssueSource (storage-agnostic, the write path for state)
' ============================================================
package "Data plane · IssueSource  (storage-agnostic; BACK-601.1)" {
  interface IssueSource <<contract>> {
    +list(filter) : Task[]
    +get(id) : Task
    +upsert(task) : void
  }
  class LocalIssueSource <<impl>> {
    '' markdown-file backed (today's Backlog.md store)
  }
  IssueSource <|.. LocalIssueSource
}
IssueSource ..> Task

' ============================================================
' PLANE 3 — PRESENTATION (human-facing, view-only projections)
' ============================================================
package "Plane 3 · presentation  (view-only, product/UX-speed)" {

  class IssueListView <<projection>> {
    +render() : swimlanes grouped by pipeline_id
    '' joins tasks ⟗ claims, applies label(...) + displayHints
  }
  class LabelProjection <<projection>> {
    +label(state, role, plane) : string   '' PURE, one-way, boundary-only
  }
  class DisplayHints <<projection>> {
    +byPipeline : Map<pipeline_id, {columns, sort, collapsed, icon, title}>
    '' references pipeline_id; does NOT live on Pipeline (ADR-011 D-2.1)
  }

  IssueListView ..> LabelProjection
  IssueListView ..> DisplayHints
}

' ---- cross-plane wiring: presentation consumes the two contracts (read-only) ----
IssueListView ..> IssueSource : list() tasks
IssueListView ..> Coordinator : claims() (live via WS)

note as N_principle
  **Three-plane principle (2026-07-04):**
  Plane 1 owns the ONLY canonical vocabulary.
  Planes 2 & 3 PROJECT from it; never define states.
  Coupling only via the two <<contract>> seams (read-only, one-way).
  UI/config strings must NEVER feed back into engine logic.
end note

@enduml
